# Tic-Tac-Toe – Instructions

## 🎮 How to Play

Tic-Tac-Toe is a two-player game played on a 3x3 grid. The first player is **X**, and the second player is **O**. Players take turns placing their symbol in an empty square. The goal is to get **three of your symbols in a row** – vertically, horizontally, or diagonally – before your opponent.

---

## 🕹 Controls

- Use your mouse to click on a square to place your X or O.
- Players alternate turns automatically.

---

## 🏁 Game End

- The game ends when one player gets three in a row.
- If all squares are filled and there’s no winner, the game ends in a **draw**.
- A message will appear showing the result.
- Use the **"Restart"** button to play again.

---

